      "name": "Evaluate Duplicate Lookup",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [1840, -220],
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Duplicate Lookup uses the node's built-in filter (filtersUI) rather than reading\n// every row, so this only inspects the (0 or 1) matches it returned - not the whole sheet.\n// NOTE: Google Sheets API has no true server-side query language; \"filtersUI\" still\n// pulls the underlying range and filters it inside the node. Verify this against your\n// n8n version's actual Google Sheets node schema before relying on it at scale - if it\n// doesn't behave as documented, replace this node with a direct Sheets API values.get\n// call scoped to the commentId column, or move dedup to Postgres/Supabase (see note below).\nconst matches = $input.all();\nconst current = $('Normalize Comment Data').first().json;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...current,\n    isDuplicate: matches.length > 0\n  }\n}];"
